Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Core, deseed, and finely dice @long green pepper{1}(deseeded and finely diced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(trimmed and leaves separated); separate leaves. Gently crush @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} in their bag into small pieces.

Heat @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion, green pepper, and @ground pork{10%ounce}. Season generously with @salt{generous} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is lightly browned and onion is slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, and @water{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pork is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== Lime Crema ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, lime zest, and juice from one lime wedge. Add @water{1%teaspoon} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Remove pan with pork filling from heat; sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Cover pan and let sit until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide lettuce leaves between #plates{}; fill with pork filling. Drizzle with lime crema and sprinkle with crushed tortilla chips. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Lettuce wraps take the place of tortillas in tonight's one-pan fajita dish. You can pile it all in your lettuce and wrap it up with a sprinkle of tortilla chips for an added level of crunch. Now all you have to do is perfect your lettuce folding technique to maximize each full bite!